🔥 High-impact feature upgrades
1. Task depth (biggest improvement)

Right now tasks are fairly flat. You could make them feel “real-world”:

Due dates + reminders
Subtasks (checklist inside a task)
Tags/labels (e.g. “work”, “personal”, “urgent”)
Priority + sorting combined (not just filter)
Recurring tasks (daily/weekly)

This alone upgrades it from “todo app” → “productivity system”.

2. Better task states

Instead of just completed: true/false:

todo
in_progress
completed
archived

Then your dashboard becomes much more meaningful.

3. Search + advanced filtering

Right now you only filter by priority.

Add:

Search by title/description
Filter by status
Filter by date range
Sort by newest/oldest/priority

This is a very common “real app” expectation.

4. Dashboard improvements

Your KPI cards are good, but you can push it further:

Weekly productivity chart (Recharts / Chart.js)
Completion rate %
“Tasks created today”
Streak (days active)

This makes the dashboard feel SaaS-level.

🧠 Backend improvements (important for scaling)
5. Data validation layer

Right now validation is manual. Upgrade with:

Zod / Joi / express-validator

This makes your API production-safe.

6. Pagination

Tasks endpoint should not return everything forever:

GET /tasks?page=1&limit=10
Add sorting + pagination metadata
7. Centralized error handling

Instead of repeated try/catch everywhere:

Use a global error middleware

Cleaner backend structure.

8. Security upgrades
Rate limiting (login/register)
Password strength validation
Refresh tokens (optional but impressive)
HTTP-only cookies instead of localStorage (advanced)
🎨 Frontend polish (what makes it “feel premium”)
9. Loading + empty states

You already have basic loading, but improve UX:

Skeleton loaders for tasks
Empty state illustrations (“No tasks yet”)
10. Optimistic UI updates

Instead of refetching every time:

Update UI instantly on create/edit/delete
Sync in background

Feels much faster.

11. Drag & drop task board (big wow factor)

Turn Tasks into columns:

Todo | In Progress | Done

Use:

dnd-kit or react-beautiful-dnd

This is a huge portfolio upgrade.

12. Mobile responsiveness

You have some breakpoints already, but:

Sidebar collapse on mobile
Bottom nav for mobile UX
Better touch spacing
🚀 “SaaS level” enhancements (optional but impressive)
Teams / shared tasks
Role-based access (admin/user)
Activity log (who did what)
Notifications system
Email reminders
Export tasks to CSV/PDF
Dark/light theme toggle (you already have variables, so easy win)
🧩 Code quality upgrades
Move repeated API calls into a service layer
Use React Query (huge improvement over manual fetching)
Memoize expensive filters (useMemo)
Component splitting (TaskCard is good, but Tasks page can be cleaner)